Armor Expertise	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ReaverClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:From 1st level owards, the reaver may ignore the armor check penalties of many lighter types of armor. Everytime this class feature is gained, the reaver may ignore armor check penalties of up to the number listed in the poarenthesis. This feature doesn't affect higher armor check penalties in any way.	KEY:Reaver ~ Armor Expertise				DEFINE:ArmorExpertise|0					BONUS:VAR|ArmorExpertise|1|PREVARGTEQ:ReaverLVL,1	BONUS:VAR|ArmorExpertise|1|PREVARGTEQ:ReaverLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|ArmorExpertise|1|PREVARGTEQ:ReaverLVL,9														ASPECT:NAME|Armor Expertise (%1)|ArmorExpertise	SORTKEY:Class_Reaver	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Inspire Crew	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ReaverClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Reavers are skilled not only in boarding actions, but also in encouraging their crews to fight to best effect. A crew led by a reaver are likely to believe they are invincible and will never be defeated. From 2nd level, the reaver grants the crew he leads the morale bonus listed on the table below to their attack and damage rolls (+%1). This only applies during boarding action and if the reaver flees or is killed during the battle, this morale bonus will immediately be converted into a morale penalty, affecting the crew's attack and damage rolls.|InspireCrewBonus	KEY:Reaver ~ Inspire Crew				DEFINE:InspireCrewBonus|0					BONUS:VAR|InspireCrewBonus|(ReaverLVL+2)/4																	SORTKEY:Class_Reaver	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Bonus Feat	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ReaverClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 3rd and 8th level, the reaver may choose a bonus feat from the following list. Any prerequisites for these feats must be met in the normal way before they may be choosen.	KEY:Reaver ~ Bonus Feat									BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Reaver Bonus Feat|1|PREVARGTEQ:ReaverLVL,3	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Reaver Bonus Feat|1|PREVARGTEQ:ReaverLVL,8																SORTKEY:Class_Reaver	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Instill Fear	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ReaverClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When the reaver reaches the 4th level, he gains the extraordinary ability to cast Fear as a free action once per day. This ability may only be used during a boarding action and the reaver must perform some dramatic and morale-building action in view of his crew and his enemies in the action it is used. This ability has a range of 5 feet per class level of the reaver (%1 feet) and all within range will be frightened foir 1d6 rounds. Those who pass Will save (DC %1) will merely be shaken for this time. This ability may only be used %1/day.|InstillFearRange|InstillFearDC|InstillFearTimes	KEY:Reaver ~ Instill Fear				DEFINE:InstillFearRange|0	DEFINE:InstillFearDC|0	DEFINE:InstillFearTimes|0			BONUS:VAR|InstillFearRange|5*ReaverLVL	BONUS:VAR|InstillFearDC|DefaultSpellDCCha+ReaverLVL	BONUS:VAR|InstillFearTimes|1															SORTKEY:Class_Reaver	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Skilled Boarder	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ReaverClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Reavers are the masters of boarding actions and well-respected by their captains. At 7th level, the reaver may add his class level to the opposed Seamanship check required in boarding actions, whether his ship is the attacker or defender.	KEY:Reaver ~ Skilled Boarder																										SORTKEY:Class_Reaver	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
